
[1]long-sightedness

   LONG-SIGHTEDNESS, n.

   1. The faculty of seeing objects at a great distance.

   2. In medicine, presbyopy; that defect of sight by which objects near
   at hand are seen confusedly, but at remoter distances distinctly.
